					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13442436#post-4697544</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13442436/scp-5096#post-4697544</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2020 10:24:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Harpsichord23</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4257415</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>&quot;Why can't you just make the book magic, with a non-butterfly me?&quot;</p> <p>&quot;Butterflies work in mysterious ways, Jane! Ƹ̵̡Ӝ̵̨̄Ʒ&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>This whole thing was really charming.</p> <p>My only complaint would be that the 2nd paragraph of the description feels totally unnecessary. I know that you had to incorporate the soil and garden-party stuff from the conprocs, but that doesn't stop it from feeling like a speedbump. Maybe if the duplication/transmutation came up again later I'd feel differently but as it stands now I think the article would be improved by dropping it entirely. The quicker a reader gets to the fantastic addenda the quicker they're going to be hooked for the entire thing.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13442436#post-4697444</guid>
				<title>Re: Author post  Ƹ̵̡Ӝ̵̨̄Ʒ</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13442436/scp-5096#post-4697444</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2020 08:16:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>GreyPercival</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1856921</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Speaking of butterflies, seeing my containment procedures in someone else's SCP doc? That truly gave <em>me</em> butterflies. I was scanning through the contest posts to see if someone had posted it, and lo, here it is!</p> <p>Can't say I was expecting my wonky procedures to create this SCP, but I'm pleasantly surprised. Apologies if you found it a bit too limiting.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
